Standard Operating Procedure

High flow nasal oxygen during conscious sedation in the cardiac catheterisation laboratory: A randomized controlled trial

Post-procedure Data Collection - Version 1

Introduction

This document outlines the procedures for post-procedure data collection for the study. It also outlines instructions for using REDCap software.

Procedures

  1. After the procedure is completed, the Research Coordinator will collect the data collection form from the Anesthesia Assistant and check that all fields have been completed. If any missing data are identified, the Research Coordinator is to query the Anesthesia Assistant regarding the missing items.
  2. The Research Coordinator will enter the data collected in this paper-based form into REDCap as soon as possible after the procedure.
  3. The Research Coordinator will also enter a description of any adverse effects of the oxygen delivery device into REDCap.
  4. After the participant has reached phase 2 post-anesthetic recovery, the Research Coordinator will provide the participant with a paper-based data collection form. The form will contain the Iowa Satisfaction with Anesthesia Scale items along with instruction for how it should be completed. After the participant has completed the form, the Research Coordinator will inspect it to ensure that all items have been completed and provide an opportunity for the participant to revise it if any missing items are identified.
  5. The Research Coordinator will enter the data into the REDCap database as soon as possible after it has been collected.
